==In popular culture==
Due to its proximity to several film studios including those at [[Pinewood Studios|Pinewood]], the airfield has been used to represent outside locations in a number of feature films. The [[James Bond]] films ''[[Goldfinger (film)|Goldfinger]]'', ''[[Thunderball (film)|Thunderball]]'' and ''[[Octopussy]]'' were all filmed at Northolt with station personnel serving as extras in the ''Octopussy'' hangar fly-through scene. The TV mini series ''[[The Winds of War]]'', ''[[The Bill]]'' and the BBC shows ''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]'', ''[[Doctor Who]]'' and ''[[Red Dwarf]]'' have all used Northolt to represent various fictional airfields.<ref name="Bristow"/> In early 2010 the station was used for the filming of the BBC's final series of ''[[Ashes to Ashes (TV series)|Ashes to Ashes]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iwcp.co.uk/news/news/the-iw-might-be-but-its-car-is-a-star-in-finale-32929.aspx |title=The IW might be **** but its car is a star in finale |author=Martin Neville |date=21 May 2010 |work= |publisher=Isle of Wight County Press |accessdate=14 September 2010}}</ref>

